    "scripture": [
      "The ship was industrial. The ocean made it art.",
      "The chamber holds water now. The water holds sound.",
      "bodyFeedback=0.5: the steel room remembers every note it ever heard."
    ],
    "revelation": null,
    "god": null,
    "flock_note": "WRECK macro dials in the metal chamber presence. Lower WRECK for more open water — the ship dissolves back into the ocean. Raise PRESSURE to add depth compression: the deeper the chamber, the more the walls press in. The wreck at maximum PRESSURE is barely distinguishable from the trench floor.",
    "diagnosis": "bodyChar=2 (Wreck): short comb + allpass diffusion, the precise acoustic signature of hollow metal rooms. bodyFeedback=0.5: moderate — the chamber sustains but does not overwhelm. filterRes=0.5 with filterCutoff=180: dark resonant character, the wreck has been submerged for decades. Industrial archaeology, not industrial music."
  },
